{
  "format": "tiptap/v1",
  "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T17:53:08.045Z",
  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Transformers have no inherent sense of token order. "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Positional encoding",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "bold"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " injects position information into embeddings so the model distinguishes \"delete file A then B\" from \"delete file B then A\"—essential for agent plans, shell commands, and ordered tool chains."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What it is"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Given token embedding "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "x_i"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " at position "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "i"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ", the input to the first layer is often "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "x_i + p_i"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (additive encoding) or "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "\\text{RoPE}(x_i, i)"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (rotary encoding applied inside attention). "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "p_i"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is a vector encoding position."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Why it matters"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Self-attention alone is permutation-invariant: shuffling tokens would yield the same set of pairwise interactions (without positional signal). Agents depend on order—conversation turns, stack traces, pipeline stages—so position encoding is not optional."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "How it works"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Sinusoidal (original Transformer)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Fixed waves of varying frequency: even dimensions use sine, odd use cosine of "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "i / 10000^{2k/d}"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Relative offsets can be inferred from linear combinations of encodings at positions "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "i"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "j"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Learned absolute embeddings"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A lookup table "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "E_{\\text{pos}}[i]"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " trained end-to-end, capped by maximum length "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "L_{\\max}"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". Simple but does not extrapolate beyond trained lengths."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rotary Position Embedding (RoPE)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rotates query and key vectors by position-dependent angles so dot products depend on "
          },
          {
            "type": "inlineMath",
            "attrs": {
              "latex": "i - j"
            }
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (relative distance). Used in LLaMA, Mistral, and many agent-facing open models. Extends more gracefully to longer contexts with scaling tricks (NTK, YaRN)."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trade-offs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Absolute learned",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — simple; poor length extrapolation"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Sinusoidal",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — no extra params; less common in modern LLMs"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "RoPE",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": " — strong relative bias; needs context-extension methods for very long agent threads"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to use which"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When selecting a base model for an agent, RoPE-based decoder models are the common default. Context-window claims (128k, 1M) reflect extrapolation methods, not unlimited reliable recall—position encoding quality still limits effective use."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Real-world example"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An agent must run tools in order: fetch customer → validate ID → charge card. If positional signal were absent, the model might treat the three tool results as an unordered bag. Position encoding plus causal attention preserves temporal structure in the transcript."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Assuming longer context window equals reliable access to all tokens"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Concatenating documents without clear separators—position alone does not replace structure"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Mixing chat templates that reorder messages without understanding position impact"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key takeaways"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Attention is order-blind without positional information"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Modern LLMs favor RoPE for relative position in attention"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Agent workflows with strict ordering depend on this mechanism"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Context extension is an active research area, not a solved scaling knob"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
